==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Posit
<hw>Pos"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Posited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Positing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>ponere</ets>,
<ets>positum</ets>, to place. See <er>Position</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To dispose or set firmly or fixedly; to place or dispose in
relation to other objects.</def> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>To assume as real or conceded;
<as>as, to <ex>posit</ex> a principle</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Position</ent>⟦br⟧
